thread.title: One passenger dead after Southwest engine failure

title: One passenger dead after Southwest engine failure
text:
One passenger dead after Southwest engine failure Tuesday, April 17, 2018 - 01:19 
A Dallas-bound Southwest Airlines Co with 148 people aboard made an emergency landing on Tuesday at Philadelphia International Airport after suffering engine failure, and one person died, according to the airline and U.S. officials.
